    reference (separate web resources for heavy libs); (3) link to the R3 bundle-size investigation memo
    (find under `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/`). Per OC-R4-04 this is **amendment
    only** — no separate-web-resources implementation. Do not propose or commit implementation work.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Architecture documentation author. The amendment is light-touch — adding a clearly bounded subsection
    to an existing ADR. Do NOT rewrite the base ADR or change existing stage definitions.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Two files modified: `.claude/adr/ADR-026-stage-lifecycle.md` (concise, +20-30 lines for the new
